The paper deals with the problem of pliable-index-coding, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT) that deals with the efficient transmission of information to multiple receivers with side information. The use of absent receivers to construct decoding chains with skipped messages suggests a focus on network coding (cs.NI) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also considers problems that are not complete-S, which suggests a focus on coding theory (cs.SI) and communication complexity (cs.CC).
